name: WestJet 767-338ER [C-FWAD] Taxi and Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
On the last day of January, WestJet's third 767 took flight with passengers for the first time to Toronto. This aircraft, formerly VH-OGL, will join former VH-OGN and VH-OGJ in service doing YYC-YYZ rotations, Alberta-Hawaii flights, and Saturday YYZ-MBJ rotations. This video includes the aircraft taxiing and taking off from runway 35L as "WestJet 670 heavy". Enjoy!

Thanks for watching! Please comment, rate, and subscribe!
